Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle over the @Chinese Five Spice{1%sachet}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}
or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{}
or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the
@breadcrumbs{50%g} into another #bowl{} and season with the @salt{¼%tsp} and
@pepper{}.

Season the chicken, then dip it into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring
it's completely coated.

Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom
of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3
> mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven
until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Discard the oil and wipe out the pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper and onion and fry until just soft,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @sliced burger buns{2} into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and
@sriracha sauce{15%g}.

> TIP: Leave some mayo plain for those who'd like it.

Add the garlic and @chilli flakes{1%pinch} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder) to the pan and stir-fry, ~{30%seconds} more. Remove from the heat.

Once your chips are ready, add them to the pan of veg along with the
@sugar{2%tsp}. Toss everything together.

Spread the sriracha mayo over the bun bases. Top with the chicken, then
sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve with your spice bag chips alongside.

Enjoy!